    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Java has this implemented for <code>BigInteger</code> and <code>BigDecimal</code> as <code>divideAndRemainder</code>:<br />\nThese are meant for huge integers and decimal numbers, rather than extreme efficiency, though, and using them instead of <code>int</code> or <code>long</code> will be costly. Usage e.g.:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>BigInteger a = BigInteger.valueOf(1234);\nBigInteger b = BigInteger.valueOf(321);\nBigInteger[] result = a.divideAndRemainder(b);\nBigInteger div = result[0];\nBigInteger mod = result[1];\n</code></pre>\n<p>Note that java is a high-level programming language. Optimization happens in JVM, so possibly a sequence of division and remainder can result in a <code>divmod</code> instruction.</p>\n<p>If you however want some complex algorithm where exact instructions are important, write a library in C (perhaps even using some Assembler) and use it in Java through Java Native Interface. Note that you will need to provide binaries for every platform.</p>\n"
  }, {
