  "question_id" : 46905740,
  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46905740/does-java-have-a-divmod-instruction",
  "title" : "Does java have a divmod instruction?",
  "body" : "<p>Besides <code>divmod</code> being a native instruction on many chipsets, it also is a lot easier on the eyes when subdividing a number in multiple different denominations</p>\n\n<p>(which happens with e.g. milliseconds -> datetime conversion, or cents -> coin denomination conversion).</p>\n\n<p>So is there a <code>divmod</code> that returns both the result of the division and of the remainder at the same time?</p>\n"
}